I liked to imagine what would happen if, on a particularly stormy day, the wind picked me and raised me up to the sky,  above the eroded Soviet buildings, and took me to some faraway lands, where only the wind leads, where adventure rages on and dragons sleep in river caves.

Where I live, the autumn wind is VERY strong, specifically in front of my building - it often turns into a dust devil.

When I was a very small kid, my mum had to hold me or the wind would often be too powerful for me and would push me around or throw me on the ground.

Few summers ago had my niece experience something like this. Was at my village with the family, and our house is near the forests and the pastures, all cows of the village pass through our street every evening on their road to the individual houses/farms. So I took my niece and..

... put her in our car which was parked on the street, with the cows passing centimeters away from it. She had never seen such animals from up close and I remember the ABSOLUTELY fascinated look on her face looking at the cows and the bulls friendly passing next to her- amazing!
